            . I am a <rs id="t18301209-35-viclabel208" type="occupation">surgeon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-35-victim408 t18301209-35-viclabel208"></join>. On the 4th of December I was in <placeName id="t18301209-35-crimeloc209">Brydges-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-35-crimeloc209" type="placeName" value="Brydges-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-35-crimeloc209" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-35-off206 t18301209-35-crimeloc209"></join>, returning from the theatre, between twelve and one o'clock; I felt the flap of my coat fall against my thigh - I said, "Some one has taken my handkerchief;" a coachman said the prisoner was the man - he was taken, and my handkerchief found on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-35-person410">
                  TIMOTHY 
                  McCARTY
               <interp inst="t18301209-35-person410" type="surname" value="McCARTY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-35-person410" type="given" value="TIMOTHY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-35-person410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was on duty, and took the prisoner - the handkerchief was found, but I did not see it in his possession; I found this other handkerchief in his hat, and this duplicate.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-35-person411">
                  GEORGE 
                  HARRINGTON
               <interp inst="t18301209-35-person411" type="surname" value="HARRINGTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-35-person411" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-35-person411" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a hackney-coachman. I saw the prosecutor walking down the street; the prisoner stepped behind him, and took his handkerchief - I pointed him out, and took him into custody; while I had hold of him, and he was saying he had not got it, two gentlemen took it from his pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. That man speaks false - I never had it at all on my person.</p>
